race.comment: SCINTILLANTE (5) jumped a double figure chance here first-up over 1427m and while he did finish off well, he ultimately ended up 3.8L off the winner. Out in trip now is a big tick and they may be able to have him a touch closer from an inside barrier. Boasts a good second-up record and can land the knockout blow. LEGEND BEAST (4) is a Kiwi import making his debut in Aus for the Lindsay Park team. He's had three jumpouts in readiness for today, winning his most recent at Pakenham. Draws the inside and if he can run up to his Kiwi form, he'll be right in the finish first-up. ACELUM (7) is looking for the hat-trick as he steps up to the mile for the first time. He's a lightly raced gelding by The Autumn Sun, so he's expected to relish the mile now. Looks an exciting prospect on the rise. MAXXI BON (15) is better than he showed last time out at Sandown and looks well placed to improve today.
